Plus there are a few issues game dynamic wise. The "harder" levels are not naturally harder. Instead of working up to a fun, strategic challenge, enemies simply and magically spawn when desired by the Dev./storyline. It is highly unlikely to pass a later level unless you remember when the staged waves are coming and then you cheat around them. You could be a good strategist, and you could have set a good board yet unless you know how many, from where, and when the extras are coming, you will likely lose and have to repeat.
